node.text: Christian Dvorak is headed to the Canadiens. Canadiens get their 2nd line centre after not matching the Jesperi Kotkaniemi offer sheet.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hockey Collective on September 04, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NEWS HOCKEY COLLECTIVE 19 15 THE CANADIENS WILL NOT MATCH THE HURRICANES OFFER SHEET TO JESPERI KOTKANIEMI. H/T MONTREAL CANADIENS'.

node.text: Kotkaniemi signs a 1 year, $6.1M deal with the Hurricanes. Montreal will receive Carolina's 1st and 3rd round 2022 Draft picks as compensation.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hockey Collective on September 02, 2021. May be an image of 4 people and text that says 'NEWS FCM HOCKEY COLLECTIVE OILERS COLBYS kidz presentedby: Ford THE OILERS HAVE ANNOUNCED THE CREATION OF COLBY'S KIDS, A PROGRAM THAT WILL PROVIDE AN OPPORTUNITY FOR ALL YOUTH TO PARTICIPATE IN THE GAME OF HOCKEY. EDMONTON OILERS'.

node.text:
Oilers Alumni Fernando Pisani, Jason Chimera and Kyle Brodziak will be leading the program and teaching the next generation of hockey players, with the support of Hockey Edmonton instructors.

Colby's Kids will be easily accessible and affordable, and will provide kids and parents with more exposure to the sport through easy-to-access skill development and learning sessions to encourage continued participation in the sport.

node.text:
Team Canada beats Team USA to win GOLD at the World Championships. Marie-Philip Poulin scores, but play continued after the buzzer didn’t sound initially. The buzzer then went off, to confirm Canada’s gold 🇨🇦
(📹: @tsn_official)
